icine%20at%20Cornell%20University's%20College%20of%20Veterinary%20Medicine%3B%20Jennifer%20Malawey%2C%20a%20certified%20dog%20trainer%20and%20behavioral%20consultant%20at%20Instinct%20Dog%20Behavior%20and%20Training%3B%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwoofsdogtraining.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELaura%20Sharkey%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20owner%20and%20senior%20trainer%20at%20Woofs!%20Dog%20Training%20Center.%20Reporter%20Shoshi%20Parks'%20experience%20as%20a%20certified%20professional%20dog%20trainer%20also%20helped%20shape%20our%20selection%20criteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20each%20type%20of%20muzzle%2C%20we%20favored%20products%20with%20the%20majority%2C%20if%20not%20all%2C%20of%20the%20following%20characteristics%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBreathable%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGives%20dog%20the%20ability%20to%20pant%2C%20eat%20treats%2C%20and%20drink%20water%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMoldable%20or%20custom%20fit%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENods%20to%20comfort%20including%20the%20type%20of%20material%20used%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESecure%20straps%20and%20optional%20safety%20straps%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAvailable%20in%20multiple%20sizes%20and%20colors%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2276f49339-791f-4bae-b037-f326f4465814%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22FAQs%5C%22%3EDog%20muzzle%20FAQs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20mixed%20breed%20dog%20touches%20its%20nose%20to%20the%20muzzle%20for%20a%20treat.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F610d60652a24d00018621bfd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIt's%20important%20to%20desensitize%20a%20dog%20to%20a%20muzzle%20before%20you%20place%20it%20on%20them%20for%20an%20extended%20period%20of%20time.%3Cp%3EShoshi%20Parks%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20muzzle%20do%20vets%20recommend%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ESharkey%20says%20wearing%20a%20muzzle%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fdog-muzzle-when-how-to-use%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emay%20be%20a%20good%20idea%20for%20some%20dogs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20especially%20in%20high-stress%20situations%20like%20going%20to%20the%20vet%2C%20where%20the%20dog%20may%20pose%20a%20biting%20risk.%20The%20type%20of%20dog%20muzzle%20recommended%20by%20your%20vet%20will%20vary%2C%20but%20the%20best%20dog%20muzzles%20are%20properly%20fitted%20to%20your%20dog%20and%20keep%20them%20and%20people%20safe%20in%20triggering%20situations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20it%20cruel%20to%20muzzle%20a%20dog%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ENo%2C%20it's%20not%20cruel%20to%20muzzle%20a%20dog%20likely%20to%20bite%20or%20eat%20objects%20on%20walks.%20Wearing%20a%20properly%20fitted%20muzzle%20can%20be%20as%20comfortable%20as%20wearing%20a%20harness%20or%20collar.%20%26quot%3BIn%20a%20well-acclimated%2C%20well-fit%20muzzle%2C%20a%20dog%20is%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20do%20everything%20they%20would%20normally%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Shikashio%20says.%20It's%20an%20excellent%20way%20to%20provide%20freedom%20while%20assuring%20the%20safety%20of%20your%20pup%20and%20everyone%20around%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20long%20can%20a%20dog%20wear%20a%20muzzle%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EDogs%20should%20only%20wear%20a%20muzzle%20when%20they%20need%20it.%20That%20may%20include%20on%20walks%2C%20around%20strangers%2C%20or%20at%20the%20vet's%20office.%20A%20dog%20can%20wear%20a%20comfortable%2C%20properly%20fitted%20basket%20muzzle%20for%20a%20few%20hours%20as%20long%20as%20you%20regularly%20check%20that%20it%20is%20not%20rubbing%20or%20chafing.%20A%20sleeve%20muzzle%20that%20prevents%20a%20dog%20from%20panting%20should%20only%20be%20worn%20briefly%20during%20vet%20exams%20or%20grooming.%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20muzzles%20stop%20barking%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ESharkey%20says%20using%20a%20muzzle%20to%20stop%20barking%20or%20disruptive%20behavior%20is%20never%20appropriate.%20A%20dog%20exhibiting%20these%20behaviors%20may%20be%20experiencing%20discomfort%20or%20anxiety%2C%20and%20it's%20best%20to%20consult%20a%20canine%20behaviorist%20to%20determine%20why.%20Plus%2C%20if%20a%20dog%20can't%20bark%2C%20it%20can't%20pant%2C%20leading%20to%20dangerous%20overheating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20do%20I%20get%20my%20dog%20to%20wear%20a%20muzzle%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EDogs%20not%20properly%20introduced%20to%20a%20muzzle%20are%20likely%20to%20hate%20wearing%20one.%20Sharkey%20says%20only%20muzzling%20a%20dog%20in%20stressful%20situations%20can%20cause%20strong%20negative%20associations%20with%20it.%20To%20help%20your%20dog%20be%20comfortable%20in%20a%20muzzle%2C%20it's%20best%20to%20use%20a%20process%20of%20gradual%20desensitization.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20going%20to%20be%20something%20that%20they're%20used%20to%2C%20that%20they%20accept%20and%20tolerate%20well%2C%20and%20that%20they%20are%20reinforced%20highly%20for%20wearing%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20Our%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fhow-to-use-dog-muzzle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20how-to%20guide%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20help%20you%20properly%20acclimate%20your%20dog%20to%20wearing%20a%20muzzle.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20muzzle%20is%20best%20for%20aggressive%20dogs%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20general%2C%20Malawey%20recommends%20a%20basket%20muzzle%20for%20most%20situations.%20This%20type%20of%20muzzle%20is%20the%20safest%20for%20long%20wear%20because%20the%20dog%20can%20eat%2C%20drink%2C%20breathe%2C%20and%20pant.%20A%20basket%20muzzle%20can%20also%20prevent%20dogs%20who%20don't%20respond%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bleave%20it%26quot%3B%20cute%20from%20ingesting%20foreign%20materials%20on%20walks%20and%20curb%20biting.%20Dogs%20who%20may%20be%20reactive%20in%20stressful%20situations%2C%20like%20th