xact%20measurements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20basket%20has%20tightly%20woven%20biothane-coated%20straps%20and%20can%20be%20designed%20for%20snouts%20from%205%2F8%20to%205%201%2F2%20inches%20in%20length.%20Straps%20wrap%20around%20the%20back%20of%20the%20head%2C%20and%20an%20optional%20security%20strap%20runs%20from%20the%20top%20of%20the%20muzzle%20and%20between%20the%20ears.%20Metal%20rivets%20in%20the%20webbing%20hold%20the%20pieces%20together.%20Additional%20choices%20for%20customizing%20the%20Bumas%20include%20a%20neoprene%20nose%20piece%20or%20nose-free%20option%20for%20dogs%20with%20sensitive%20snouts%20and%20a%20simple%20click-clasp%20or%20a%20metal-buckle%20fastener.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Bumas%20Muzzles%20are%20expensive%2C%20they%20are%20among%20the%20best%20dog%20muzzles%20on%20the%20market.%20Shikashio%20also%20recommends%20them.%20He%20notes%2C%20however%2C%20that%20because%20the%20biothane%20material%20is%20not%20100%25%20bite-proof%2C%20they%20are%20best%20for%20dogs%20that%20are%20low-level%20biters%20over%20those%20with%20a%20more%20significant%20bite%20history.%20This%20custom-made%20muzzle%20cannot%20be%20returned%20or%20exchanged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWhat%20to%20look%20for%20in%20a%20dog%20muzzle%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20few%20key%20elements%20to%20keep%20in%20mind%20when%20shopping%20for%20one%20of%20the%20best%20dog%20muzzles.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIntended%20use%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instinctdogtraining.com%2Fpersonnel%2Fjennifer-malawey%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJennifer%20Malawey%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20certified%20professional%20dog%20trainer%20and%20behavioral%20consultant%20at%20Instinct%20Dog%20Behavior%20and%20Training%2C%20says%20there%20are%20several%20reasons%20why%20a%20dog%20might%20wear%20a%20muzzle.%20It's%20important%20to%20find%20the%20one%20that%20best%20suits%20your%20dog%20and%20the%20situation.%20For%20example%2C%20brief%20trips%20to%20the%20vet%20may%20only%20require%20a%20soft%20sleeve%20muzzle%20intended%20for%20short-term%20wear%2C%20while%20a%20basket%20muzzle%20might%20be%20best%20for%20longer%20walks.%20All%20muzzles%20used%20for%20extended%20wear%20must%20allow%20the%20dog%20to%20comfortably%20breathe%2C%20pant%2C%20drink%20water%2C%20and%20accept%20treats%2C%20Malawey%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFit%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20best%20dog%20muzzles%20will%20stay%20securely%20on%20your%20dog's%20head%2C%20Malawey%20says.%20Muzzles%20should%20have%20adjustable%20straps%20to%20loosen%20or%20tighten%20for%20a%20better%20fit.%20If%20you're%20opting%20for%20a%20muzzle%20without%20customization%20options%2C%20Malawey%20recommends%20moldable%20muzzles.%20They%20can%20help%20achieve%20a%20more%20secure%20fit%20in%20most%20dogs.%20Another%20aspect%20to%20consider%20is%20snout%20length.%20Large%20and%20small%20breeds%20will%20have%20different%20muzzle%20requirements%2C%20so%20avoid%20anything%20that's%20considered%20one%20size%20fits%20all.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaterial%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Durable%20materials%20like%20rubber%20and%20biothane%20are%20good%20options%20for%20the%20best%20dog%20muzzles.%20For%20sleeve%20muzzles%2C%20synthetic%20mesh%20typically%20works%20well%20to%20ensure%20airflow.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EExtra%20features%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Muzzles%20with%20extra%20safety%20straps%20may%20be%20useful%20in%20keeping%20a%20dog%20safe%2C%20but%20they%20are%20unnecessary.%20Options%20with%20fun%20colors%20or%20designs%20may%20also%20be%20a%20good%20choice%2C%20especially%20if%20you%20want%20to%20avoid%20some%20of%20the%20stigma%20of%20muzzling%20a%20dog.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHow%20we%20selected%20the%20best%20dog%20muzzles%3Cp%3EWe%20made%20our%20choices%20for%20this%20guide%20based%20on%20recommendations%20and%20advice%20from%20Michael%20Shikashio%2C%20a%20certified%20animal%20behaviorist%20and%20dog%20aggression%20expert%3B%20Dr.%20Katherine%20Houpt%2C%20a%20veterinary%20behaviorist%20and%20professor%20emeritus%20of%20behavior%20medicine%20at%20Cornell%20University's%20College%20of%20Veterinary%20Medicine%3B%20Jennifer%20Malawey%2C%20a%20certified%20dog%20trainer%20and%20behavioral%20consultant%20at%20Instinct%20Dog%20Behavior%20and%20Training%3B%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwoofsdogtraining.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELaura%20Sharkey%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20owner%20and%20senior%20trainer%20at%20Woofs!%20Dog%20Training%20Center.%20Reporter%20Shoshi%20Parks'%20experience%20as%20a%20certified%20professional%20dog%20trainer%20also%20helped%20shape%20our%20selection%20criteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20each%20type%20of%20muzzle%2C%20we%20favored%20products%20with%20the%20majority%2C%20if%20not%20all%2C%20of%20the%20following%20characteristics%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBreathable%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGives%20dog%20the%20ability%20to%20pant%2C%20eat%20treats%2C%20and%20drink%20water%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMoldable%20or%20custom%20fit%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENods%20to%20comfort%20including%20the%20type%20of%20material%20used%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESecure%20straps%20and%20optional%20safety%20straps%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAvailable%20in%20multiple%20sizes%20and%20colors%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDog%20muzzle%20FAQs%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20mixed%20breed%20dog%20touches%20its%20nose%20to%20the%20muzzle%20for%20a%20treat.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F610d60652a24d00018621bfd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIt's%20important%20to%20desensitize%20a%20dog%20to%20a%20muzzle%20before%20you%20place%20it%20on%20them%20for%20an%20extended%20period%20of%20time.%3Cp%3EShoshi%20Parks%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20it%20cruel%20to%20muzzle%20a%20dog%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ENo%2C%20it's%20not%20cruel%20to%20muzzle%20a%20dog%20likely%20to%20bite%20or%20eat%20objects%20on%20walks.%20Wearing%20a%20properly%20fitted%20muzzle%20can%20be%20as%20comfortable%20as%20wearing%20a%20harness%20or%20collar.%20%26quot%3BIn%20a%20well-acclimated%2C%20well-fit%20muzzle%2C%20a%20dog%20is%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20do%20everything%20they%20would%20normally%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Shikashio.%20It's%20an%20excellent%20way%20to%20provide%20freedom%20while%20assuring%20the%20safety%20of%20your%20pup%20and%20everyone%20around%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20long%20can%20a%20dog%20wear%20a%20muzzle%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EDogs%20should%20only%20wear%20a%20muzzle%20when%20they%20need%20it.%20That%20may%20include%20on%20walks%2C%20around%20strangers%2C%20or%20at%20the%20vet's%20office.%20A%20dog%20can%20wear%20a%20comfortable%2C%20properly%20fitted%20basket%20muzzle%20for%20a%20few%20hours%20as%20long%20as%20you%20regularly%20check%20that%20it%20is%20not%20rubbing%20or%20chafing.%20A%20sleeve%20muzzle%20that%20prevents%20a%20dog%20from%20panting%20should%20only%20be%20worn%20briefly%20during%20vet%20exams%20or%20grooming.%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20muzzles%20stop%20barking%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ESharkey%20says%20using%20a%20muzzle%20to%20stop%20barking%20or%20disruptive%20behavior%20is%20never%20appropriate.%20A%20dog%20exhibiting%20these%20behaviors%20may%20be%20experiencing%20discomfort%20or%20anxiety%2C%20and%20it's%20best%20to%20consult%20a%20canine%20behaviorist%20to%20determine%20why.%20Plus%2C%20if%20a%20dog%20can't%20bark%2C%20it%20can't%20pant%2C%20leading%20to%20dangerous%20overheating.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20do%20I%20get%20my%20dog%20to%20wear%20a%20muzzle%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EDogs%20not%20properly%20introduced%20to%20a%20muzzle%20are%20likely%20to%20hate%20wearing%20one.%20Sharkey%20says%20only%20muzzling%20a%20dog%20in%20stressful%20situations%20can%20