t%20as%20effective%2C%20Moss%20said%2C%20so%20older%20Americans%20may%20want%20to%20talk%20to%20their%20doctors%20about%20re-upping%20their%20immunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222ca65685-2005-471e-a618-1cdf28892bc9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EConsider%20a%20measles%20booster%20if%20you're%20unsure%20of%20your%20vaccine%20history%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20reason%20to%20consider%20a%20booster%20is%20if%20you%20can't%20confirm%20you%20had%20both%20doses%20of%20the%20vaccine%2C%20Glazier%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20that's%20the%20case%2C%20it's%20worth%20thinking%20about%20a%20precautionary%20shot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20issue%20is%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20don't%20know%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20unsure%2C%20get%20another%20one.%20There's%20no%20harm%20whatsoever.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeasles%20isn't%20something%20to%20gamble%20on%2C%20since%20it%20can%20lead%20to%20serious%20health%20consequences%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fconditions-symptoms%2Fhow-do-you-get-pneumonia%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epneumonia%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20brain%20inflammation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20the%20benign%20disease%20people%20make%20it%20out%20to%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20Glazier%20said.%20%26quot%3BSaying%20'I%20had%20measles%20and%20it%20was%20fine%2C'%20I%20liken%20it%20to%20saying%20%26quot%3BI%20never%20wore%20a%20seatbelt%2C%20and%20I%20was%20fine.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20only%20had%20one%20shot%2C%20you're%20still%20likely%20to%20have%20solid%20protection%2C%20but%20may%20want%20to%20consider%20a%20booster%20if%20you're%20immune-compromised%2C%20caring%20for%20someone%20who%20is%2C%20or%20are%20in%20a%20high-risk%20situation%2C%20such%20as%20a%20healthcare%20setting%20or%20outbreak%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20an%20individual%20judgment%20call%20in%20consultation%20with%20a%20healthcare%20provider%2C%26quot%3B%20Moss%2